  "prompt": "How can you avoid a girl who has a huge crush on you without hurting her?",
  "response": "Here are some gentle ways to handle the situation:\n\n1. Be polite but not encouraging\n- Keep interactions friendly but brief\n- Avoid one-on-one situations\n- Don't give mixed signals\n\n2. Create emotional distance\n- Be less responsive to her messages\n- Limit personal conversations\n- Stay professional/casual\n\n3. If needed, have a kind conversation\n- Be honest but gentle\n- Tell her you value her as a person\n- Make it clear you're not interested romantically\n- Avoid being harsh or embarrassing her\n\n4. Consider your existing relationship\n- If she's a classmate/coworker, maintain respectfulness\n- Don't gossip or make her feel humiliated\n\n5. Set clear boundaries\n- Politely decline invitations\n- Keep interactions group-oriented\n- Be consistent in your behavior\n\n6. If persistent, be more direct\n- Clearly but kindly explain you're not interested\n- Be firm but compassionate\n\nThe key is to be respectful, kind, and clear without being cruel or embarrassing.",
